git for windows

https://git-scm.com/downloads/win

git --version
git version 2.49.0.windows.1

git bash : unix type commands

git : lists all the git commands

1) create repository on github
2) Download on local
git clone https://github.com/devendra2689/financeproject.git
3) go to repository
4) git status
    => If I add a new file then it shows as untracked
    => If I modify an existing file, then it shows modified

1. make chnages to existing files / add new files (unstaged)
2. we have to stage the changes (so that they are to be committed)
3. we can commit all the staged changes

